---
title: Creamy Chicken & Bacon Spaghetti with Garlic, Parmesan & Tuscan Roasted Tomatoes
description: Love chicken alfredo? Then you’ll adore this dreamy dish. It’s a sophisticated riff on the classic with tons of flavor infused into every bite. There’s Tuscan-spiced chicken, oven-roasted garlic and tomatoes, and al dente spaghetti all coated in a creamy, cheesy sauce. It’s one of those hearty, soul-warming dishes that’s sure to put a smile on any pasta-lover’s face.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/675743c5daedc2bd1295827f-f9a73627.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/675743c5daedc2bd1295827f-en-US.pdf
servings: 2
course: main course
time required: 40 minutes
cuisine: Southern Europe
nutrition:
  calories: 1140 kcal
  fat: 69 g
  saturated fat: 28 g
  carbohydrates: 68 g
  sugar: 6 g
  protein: 54 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 820 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/creamy-chicken-and-bacon-spaghetti-675743c5daedc2bd1295827f
author: Michelle Doll Olson
---

Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 400 degrees. Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Cut each @tomato{2} into 6 wedges. Place whole @garlic{1%clove} in a small piece of #aluminum foil{} and drizzle with @olive oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}; cinch into a packet.

Drizzle a foil-lined #baking sheet{} with @cooking oil{}, then place tomato wedges on it skin side down. Coat with a drizzle of olive oil, @Tuscan Heat Spice{1%tsp} (you'll use more Tuscan Heat Spice later), salt, and pepper. Place garlic pouch next to tomatoes. Roast on middle rack until tomatoes are just wilted, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Heat a medium dry pan over medium-high heat. Add @bacon{4%oz}; cook, turning occasionally and adjusting heat if browning too quickly, until crispy, ~{6-10%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}. Wipe out pan. Once cool enough to handle, roughly chop.

Once water is boiling, add @spaghetti{6%oz} to #pot{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Reserve 3/4 cup pasta cooking water (11/2 cups for 4 servings), then drain. Keep empty pot handy for Step 5.

While spaghetti cooks, pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with paper towels. Season both sides with @Tuscan Heat Spice{1%tsp} (you'll use the rest in Step 5), salt, and pepper.

Heat a large drizzle of olive oil in pan used for bacon over medium-high heat. Cook chicken until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; cover to keep warm.

> TIP: If you don't have a lid, you can tent loosely with aluminum foil.

Once garlic is done roasting, carefully remove from pouch. Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in pot used for pasta over medium heat. Add @Tuscan Heat Spice{1%tsp} and roasted garlic; mash with the back of a #spoon{}.

Stir in 2/3 cup reserved pasta cooking water, @cream cheese{4%tbsp}, half the @parmesan cheese{3%tbsp} (save the rest for garnish), and @butter{2%tbsp} (1 cup pasta cooking water and 3 TBSP butter for 4 servings), until smooth. Turn off heat; season with salt and pepper.

Add spaghetti to pot with sauce; toss until pasta is evenly coated. If necessary, stir in more pasta cooking water a splash at a time until everything is coated in a creamy sauce. Season with salt and pepper.

Slice chicken and serve on top of spaghetti alongside roasted tomatoes. Garnish with bacon and remaining Parmesan. Serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165º.

> Pork is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.